WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.175 --> 00:00:02.350
[Boyd] Previously onFrom...

2
00:00:02.480 --> 00:00:04.308
[Kenny] I feel like I'm hanging
on by a thread here.

3
00:00:05.483 --> 00:00:07.442
[Sobbing]
Those things. they never run.

4
00:00:07.572 --> 00:00:10.401
They know there's only
so many places we can go.

5
00:00:10.532 --> 00:00:13.491
I think we're running out of
spaces on the board. Sheriff.

6
00:00:13.622 --> 00:00:15.363
I wish you had the luxury of
grief. but you don't. Boyd.

7
00:00:15.493 --> 00:00:18.366
These people need you.

8
00:00:18.496 --> 00:00:21.282
You need to be the one
to lead these people home.

9
00:00:21.412 --> 00:00:23.806
'Cause if you don't.
she died for nothing.

10
00:00:23.936 --> 00:00:25.721
[Boyd] Come on.

11
00:00:25.851 --> 00:00:27.940
Started getting tremors
in my hand a few weeks back.

12
00:00:28.071 --> 00:00:31.379
which means the clock
is officially ticking.

13
00:00:31.509 --> 00:00:33.511
but I have this crazy idea
that might actually work and--

14
00:00:33.642 --> 00:00:35.470
and if it does.

15
00:00:35.600 --> 00:00:38.734
I might be able to find a way
to get these people home.

16
00:00:38.864 --> 00:00:41.824
Something here is missing.
We just can't see it yet.

17
00:00:41.954 --> 00:00:43.217
I need something to write with.

18
00:00:43.347 --> 00:00:46.568
Ask every question. right?

19
00:00:46.698 --> 00:00:48.309
[Jade]
I don't just sit around

20
00:00:48.439 --> 00:00:50.876
fucking accepting the world
as it is!

21
00:00:51.007 --> 00:00:52.878
-[Radio static]
-Someone is doing this.

22
00:00:53.009 --> 00:00:54.619
and I'm not gonna rest
until I figure out how.

23
00:00:54.750 --> 00:00:55.881
[Kenny] Jade!

24
00:00:56.012 --> 00:01:00.147
[Gasping rapidly]

25
00:01:00.277 --> 00:01:02.410
I really like you.

26
00:01:02.540 --> 00:01:06.327
and what's about to happen.
it's gonna save everyone.

27
00:01:06.457 --> 00:01:08.329
[Ethan] Where's my mom?
I want my mom!

28
00:01:08.459 --> 00:01:10.200
You're doing this for her!

29
00:01:10.331 --> 00:01:12.246
Let him go.

30
00:01:12.376 --> 00:01:13.595
They told me this
was the last one.

31
00:01:13.725 --> 00:01:15.205
then everyone gets to go home!

32
00:01:15.336 --> 00:01:16.554
[Grunts]

33
00:01:16.685 --> 00:01:17.773
-Ethan. run!
-No!

34
00:01:17.903 --> 00:01:19.688
You don't understand!

35
00:01:19.818 --> 00:01:21.690
-Nathan!
-Nathan.

36
00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:22.691
Nathan. please!

37
00:01:25.737 --> 00:01:27.609
[Jim] Where is she?

38
00:01:27.739 --> 00:01:29.219
She ran off into the woods.

39
00:01:29.350 --> 00:01:31.439
And?

40
00:01:31.569 --> 00:01:34.268
And if she comes back before
dark. then we'll handle it.

41
00:01:34.398 --> 00:01:36.444
And if she doesn't?

42
00:01:36.574 --> 00:01:38.837
If she doesn't.
then it's handled.

43
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

44
00:01:49.065 --> 00:01:53.504
[Shovel thudding]

45
00:01:53.635 --> 00:02:00.337
♪

46
00:02:00.468 --> 00:02:04.428
[Father Khatri] Chaos and faith.

47
00:02:04.559 --> 00:02:07.953
that is the duality
of our existence.

48
00:02:08.084 --> 00:02:10.478
from the moment we first arrive.

49
00:02:10.608 --> 00:02:13.698
and not simply
here in this town...

50
00:02:15.918 --> 00:02:19.791
...but in this world.
in this life.

51
00:02:19.922 --> 00:02:22.664
From the moment
we open our newborn eyes.

52
00:02:22.794 --> 00:02:27.495
we are faced with a chaos we
cannot even begin to understand.

53
00:02:27.625 --> 00:02:30.019
And how do we respond?

54
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:33.631
What is the very
first sound we make?

55
00:02:33.762 --> 00:02:35.546
We cry out.

56
00:02:36.939 --> 00:02:40.160
We plead for answers.

57
00:02:40.290 --> 00:02:43.902
before we even have words to
give voice to the questions.

58
00:02:45.208 --> 00:02:48.559
That's how we begin our
journey through this world -

59
00:02:48.690 --> 00:02:50.561
terrified.

60
00:02:50.692 --> 00:02:53.956
confused.

61
00:02:54.086 --> 00:02:56.959
And so. we search.
and we strive.

62
00:02:57.089 --> 00:02:59.875
and we stumble
through the chaos.

63
00:03:00.005 --> 00:03:04.488
We spend our lives looking
for signs that somewhere.

64
00:03:04.619 --> 00:03:07.970
somehow there's a meaning.

65
00:03:08.100 --> 00:03:11.626
a purpose to it all.

66
00:03:11.756 --> 00:03:14.890
And then. one day.
we find our faith.

67
00:03:16.196 --> 00:03:19.851
Our faith that we are
each here in this world.

68
00:03:19.982 --> 00:03:22.071
in this place.

69
00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:26.031
as part of God's
mysterious plan.

70
00:03:26.162 --> 00:03:30.775
In our faith. we understand
the chaos is the meaning.

71
00:03:30.906 --> 00:03:33.169
It is in our struggle.

72
00:03:33.300 --> 00:03:36.564
in our search.
that we find our purpose.

73
00:03:40.132 --> 00:03:43.048
"Trust in the Lord
with all thine heart

74
00:03:43.179 --> 00:03:45.312
and lean not unto thine
own understanding."

75
00:03:48.097 --> 00:03:49.881
-Amen.
-[Congregants] Amen.

76
00:03:59.587 --> 00:04:02.024
[Chattering indistinctly]

77
00:04:02.154 --> 00:04:05.201
It's always-- it's always nice
to see new faces.

78
00:04:05.332 --> 00:04:08.813
Yeah. I'm. um--
I just came by to give you this.

79
00:04:10.902 --> 00:04:13.775
We've been packing up
the other family's stuff.

80
00:04:13.905 --> 00:04:16.691
I figured
they were yours.

81
00:04:16.821 --> 00:04:19.433
Yeah.

82
00:04:19.563 --> 00:04:22.697
How's Ethan doing?

83
00:04:22.827 --> 00:04:25.047
Well. he's. um...

84
00:04:25.177 --> 00:04:28.224
He's scared
and confused.

85
00:04:28.355 --> 00:04:30.400
He doesn't understand why
Sara would try to hurt him.

86
00:04:30.531 --> 00:04:31.358
Mm.

87
00:04:33.011 --> 00:04:34.665
Has anyone seen her?

88
00:04:34.796 --> 00:04:37.059
Not since she ran
off into the woods.

89
00:04:37.189 --> 00:04:38.669
Mm.

90
00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:40.758
I ran after her. but...

91
00:04:40.889 --> 00:04:43.805
my knees aren't quite what
they used to be. I'm afraid.

92
00:04:44.719 --> 00:04:47.678
Do you think
she's still alive?

93
00:04:47.809 --> 00:04:49.114
It's unlikely
she survived the night.

94
00:04:49.245 --> 00:04:52.509
Those Bible passages. did you--

95
00:04:52.640 --> 00:04:54.946
did you write
those from memory?

96
00:04:55.077 --> 00:04:58.994
Yeah.
Word for word.

97
00:04:59.124 --> 00:05:01.039
It tends to stick.

98
00:05:04.956 --> 00:05:08.960
Um. what did you really come
here to ask me. Tabitha?

99
00:05:10.092 --> 00:05:11.963
[Exhales]

100
00:05:16.707 --> 00:05:18.448
How do you know
any of this is real?

101
00:05:20.711 --> 00:05:23.148
I mean...
[Exhaling sharply]

102
00:05:23.279 --> 00:05:26.064
It sounds crazy.
but are we dead? Are we alive?

103
00:05:26.195 --> 00:05:28.502
I...
[Sighing]

104
00:05:29.764 --> 00:05:32.027
Would it matter?

105
00:05:32.157 --> 00:05:35.117
I mean. for argument's sake.
let's say we're dead.

106
00:05:35.247 --> 00:05:37.685
and we're all stuck here
together in some strange.

107
00:05:37.815 --> 00:05:39.208
tormented purgatory.

108
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:43.821
What would be different?
We'd still be stuck.

109
00:05:43.952 --> 00:05:45.954
We'd still be searching
for a way to go home.

110
00:05:46.084 --> 00:05:50.132
All that would change is
the home we're searching for.

111
00:05:50.262 --> 00:05:52.656
Yeah.

112
00:05:52.787 --> 00:05:54.615
I mean. I'm guessing
I'm not the first person

113
00:05:54.745 --> 00:05:56.007
to come to you
with that question.

114
00:05:56.138 --> 00:05:57.835
Well. let's just say

115
00:05:57.966 --> 00:05:59.750
I've had plenty of chances
to work on my answer.

116
00:05:59.881 --> 00:06:01.056
Yeah.

117
00:06:02.013 --> 00:06:04.320
But if it's any
consolation to you.

118
00:06:04.451 --> 00:06:07.845
you were already here
when your vehicle crashed.

119
00:06:07.976 --> 00:06:11.893
You're alive. Tabitha.
Your family's alive.

120
00:06:12.023 --> 00:06:14.678
So you can scratch that
question off your list.

121
00:06:17.072 --> 00:06:18.987
Yeah.

122
00:06:19.117 --> 00:06:20.118
Bye.

123
00:06:20.249 --> 00:06:21.119
Yeah.

124
00:06:22.556 --> 00:06:32.435
♪

125
00:06:57.852 --> 00:06:58.722
[Match scratching]

126
00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:43.716
We need to talk.

127
00:07:48.198 --> 00:07:52.812
["Que Sera. Sera [Whatever Will
Be. Will be]" plays]

128
00:07:52.942 --> 00:07:58.208
♪

129
00:07:58.339 --> 00:08:03.039
♪ When I was
just a little boy♪

130
00:08:03.170 --> 00:08:05.389
♪ I asked my father♪

131
00:08:05.520 --> 00:08:07.740
♪ "What will I be?"♪

132
00:08:09.045 --> 00:08:11.439
♪ "Will I be handsome?"♪

133
00:08:11.569 --> 00:08:14.007
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

134
00:08:14.137 --> 00:08:17.053
♪ Here's what he said to me♪

135
00:08:18.402 --> 00:08:21.449
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

136
00:08:21.579 --> 00:08:25.061
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

137
00:08:27.847 --> 00:08:31.285
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

138
00:08:31.415 --> 00:08:34.810
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

139
00:08:36.464 --> 00:08:39.075
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

140
00:08:48.868 --> 00:08:53.481
♪ Now
I have children of my own♪

141
00:08:53.611 --> 00:08:56.005
♪ They ask their father♪

142
00:08:56.136 --> 00:08:58.225
♪ "What will I be?♪

143
00:08:59.792 --> 00:09:02.055
♪ "Will I be pretty?"♪

144
00:09:02.185 --> 00:09:04.492
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

145
00:09:04.622 --> 00:09:06.799
♪ I tell them tenderly♪

146
00:09:09.627 --> 00:09:11.978
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

147
00:09:12.108 --> 00:09:17.026
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

148
00:09:17.157 --> 00:09:21.944
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

149
00:09:22.075 --> 00:09:24.207
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

150
00:09:27.210 --> 00:09:29.604
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

151
00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:33.826
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

152
00:09:52.583 --> 00:09:54.411
You all right?

153
00:09:54.542 --> 00:09:56.587
Yeah. it--

154
00:09:56.718 --> 00:10:00.069
I'm having a hard time wrapping
my brain around it. I guess.

155
00:10:00.200 --> 00:10:02.637
I mean. it's Sara. you know?

156
00:10:02.767 --> 00:10:06.162
She was always
so thoughtful. so nice.

157
00:10:06.293 --> 00:10:09.209
-How's your mom taking it?
-It's hard.

158
00:10:09.339 --> 00:10:12.952
You know. Sara was kind of like
the daughter she never had.

159
00:10:15.824 --> 00:10:18.653
I been thinking about
what you said the other day.

160
00:10:18.783 --> 00:10:21.047
about running out
of room on the board.

161
00:10:21.177 --> 00:10:22.178
[Kenny]
I was upset.

162
00:10:22.309 --> 00:10:25.181
Well. it doesn't
mean you're wrong.

163
00:10:25.312 --> 00:10:28.097
Something's changing here.
It's like...

164
00:10:28.228 --> 00:10:30.230
like something's slipping away.

165
00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:33.494
The other night. the talisman
worked out in the RV.

166
00:10:33.624 --> 00:10:35.452
same way it does in the houses.

167
00:10:35.583 --> 00:10:37.628
And?

168
00:10:37.759 --> 00:10:39.892
And I've been thinking
that the only reason

169
00:10:40.022 --> 00:10:42.851
we haven't pushed
further into the forest

170
00:10:42.982 --> 00:10:45.636
is we didn't know
whether the talisman

171
00:10:45.767 --> 00:10:48.030
would protect us out there the
same way it does in the town.

172
00:10:49.640 --> 00:10:51.164
So...

173
00:10:51.294 --> 00:10:53.122
I'm putting
together some supplies.

174
00:10:53.253 --> 00:10:54.819
I'm gonna take the talisman

175
00:10:54.950 --> 00:10:58.040
and go out in the forest
and I'm gonna see--

176
00:10:58.171 --> 00:11:00.651
Hey!
Hey. hey. hey. hey!

177
00:11:00.782 --> 00:11:02.610
Kenny. what...

178
00:11:02.740 --> 00:11:05.700
Hey! You don't walk away
when I'm talking to you!

179
00:11:05.830 --> 00:11:07.180
Are you going alone?

180
00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:08.529
Yeah.

181
00:11:08.659 --> 00:11:10.574
And how far are you going?

182
00:11:10.705 --> 00:11:12.185
As far as it'll take me.

183
00:11:12.315 --> 00:11:14.665
I'm doin' this
to find a way out.

184
00:11:14.796 --> 00:11:17.799
find a way home.
Isn't that the point?

185
00:11:17.930 --> 00:11:18.626
Make sure we
all get home?

186
00:11:18.756 --> 00:11:20.193
Honestly?

187
00:11:20.323 --> 00:11:23.283
I'm not sure there
is a point anymore.

188
00:11:23.413 --> 00:11:26.155
But if you're in that much
of a hurry to fuckin' die.

189
00:11:26.286 --> 00:11:28.201
you should just go and do it.

190
00:11:28.331 --> 00:11:30.072
Okay?

191
00:11:40.474 --> 00:11:41.692
[Sighing]
I got everything packed up.

192
00:11:41.823 --> 00:11:43.216
It's ready to go to storage.

193
00:11:43.346 --> 00:11:45.958
Oh. okay.

194
00:11:47.655 --> 00:11:48.961
What are you up to?

195
00:11:52.181 --> 00:11:53.052
Look.

196
00:11:57.273 --> 00:11:58.579
There's no wire in here.

197
00:11:58.709 --> 00:11:59.754
What?

198
00:11:59.884 --> 00:12:02.235
In the cord.

199
00:12:02.365 --> 00:12:04.367
When you want
to splice a wire.

200
00:12:04.498 --> 00:12:05.890
you gotta strip away the coating
to get at the wire inside.

201
00:12:06.021 --> 00:12:08.719
But there's no wire.
This is...

202
00:12:08.850 --> 00:12:10.156
You know.
it's not actually a wire.

203
00:12:10.286 --> 00:12:12.201
And the plug?

204
00:12:12.332 --> 00:12:14.029
Look.

205
00:12:14.160 --> 00:12:16.901
Look.

206
00:12:17.032 --> 00:12:20.209
The outlets.
none of it makes any sense.

207
00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:21.689
I mean. these lamps.
they shouldn't work.

208
00:12:21.819 --> 00:12:23.430
Hello!

209
00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:25.432
Ah. you. uh.
rollercoaster guy.

210
00:12:25.562 --> 00:12:27.956
-I need your help.
-You don't knock?

211
00:12:28.087 --> 00:12:30.002
I'm sorry. would you like me
to take off my shoes too?

212
00:12:30.132 --> 00:12:32.352
You noticed the wire thing too.
huh? Fucking weird. right?

213
00:12:32.482 --> 00:12:35.137
You're that asshole
that almost killed us.

214
00:12:37.052 --> 00:12:39.228
Okay. look. first of all.
I wasn't driving.

215
00:12:39.359 --> 00:12:41.317
Second. my best friend.

216
00:12:41.448 --> 00:12:43.363
who I've known since fourth
grade. is dead. All right?

217
00:12:43.493 --> 00:12:45.539
He's not walking around with
A little boo-boo on his leg.

218
00:12:45.669 --> 00:12:47.541
So. how about we
just call that one even. okay?

219
00:12:47.671 --> 00:12:50.892
Now. you guys wanna play house
or do you wanna go home?

220
00:12:51.023 --> 00:12:53.068
Because I have an idea.

221
00:12:55.940 --> 00:12:57.551
Did you know there's
not a single copy

222
00:12:57.681 --> 00:13:00.728
of the Bible in town?

223
00:13:00.858 --> 00:13:04.036
I mean. in our little
traveler's library in the diner.

224
00:13:04.166 --> 00:13:08.214
there's at least a dozen Robert
Ludlum and Judy Blume novels.

225
00:13:08.344 --> 00:13:10.825
yet...

226
00:13:10.955 --> 00:13:13.523
not a single copy of
the world's most popular book.

227
00:13:19.616 --> 00:13:22.054
I imagine you wonder
why you're here.

228
00:13:23.751 --> 00:13:26.536
You've done such
unspeakable things.

229
00:13:31.019 --> 00:13:33.761
And by the rules of the town.
you should be in the box.

230
00:13:43.901 --> 00:13:45.468
Nathan told me
about the voices.

231
00:13:50.343 --> 00:13:51.866
It's okay.

232
00:13:58.655 --> 00:14:03.573
Sara. what if I
were to tell you

233
00:14:03.704 --> 00:14:07.534
that despite the horrible
things you've done.

234
00:14:07.664 --> 00:14:10.711
you can still help
the people of this town?

235
00:14:10.841 --> 00:14:14.367
You could still
do something good.

236
00:14:14.497 --> 00:14:17.587
I think Nathan would
like that. don't you?

237
00:14:18.893 --> 00:14:19.763
Yeah?

238
00:14:22.418 --> 00:14:23.724
Good.

239
00:14:29.860 --> 00:14:31.253
Those are pretty.

240
00:14:31.384 --> 00:14:32.689
Right?

241
00:14:32.820 --> 00:14:34.038
You have a good eye.
Miss Matthews.

242
00:14:34.169 --> 00:14:35.431
Oh. I just found
them like this.

243
00:14:35.562 --> 00:14:36.911
Like what?

244
00:14:37.041 --> 00:14:39.131
Arranged like this.

245
00:14:39.261 --> 00:14:41.742
They were on the porch
on the side of the house.

246
00:14:41.872 --> 00:14:44.005
Huh.

247
00:14:44.136 --> 00:14:47.530
Well. it seems we have a phantom
florist running around.

248
00:14:47.661 --> 00:14:48.879
Come on. It's laundry day.

249
00:14:49.010 --> 00:14:50.359
[Gasps]

250
00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:52.318
[Laughs]
Come on.

251
00:14:56.844 --> 00:14:57.932
[Jade] Ow!

252
00:14:58.062 --> 00:15:00.543
Motherfucker! Come on!

253
00:15:00.674 --> 00:15:01.501
Ugh.

254
00:15:04.156 --> 00:15:06.070
These people are ding-dongs.
They stripped the car.

255
00:15:06.201 --> 00:15:08.377
They leave behind the only
parts that actually matter.

256
00:15:08.508 --> 00:15:09.465
They're not all ding-dongs.

257
00:15:09.596 --> 00:15:10.423
Battery's gone.

258
00:15:10.553 --> 00:15:11.902
Huh?

259
00:15:12.033 --> 00:15:13.600
I said.
the battery is gone.

260
00:15:16.037 --> 00:15:17.952
That means we gotta
go back to town.

261
00:15:18.082 --> 00:15:20.737
Wait. just as soon
as I get this cable here.

262
00:15:20.868 --> 00:15:22.043
Goddamn it. come on.

263
00:15:22.841 --> 00:15:26.322
Why all the way out here?

264
00:15:26.453 --> 00:15:29.673
We literally could've gotten
wiring from any car in town.

265
00:15:29.804 --> 00:15:33.634
My friend. this is
a top-of-the-line Audi Q5.

266
00:15:33.764 --> 00:15:35.941
Parts sourced from--

267
00:15:36.071 --> 00:15:38.508
You really wanna pin our hopes
to some peasant model jalopy?

268
00:15:39.770 --> 00:15:40.597
Yep.

269
00:15:42.208 --> 00:15:43.078
You got all that?

270
00:15:46.255 --> 00:15:48.127
Whoo!
We're doing it!

271
00:15:48.257 --> 00:15:49.302
Science!

272
00:16:00.704 --> 00:16:03.185
[Sighing]
Good morning.

273
00:16:03.316 --> 00:16:05.013
Uh. I'm dropping
these off for storage.

274
00:16:18.070 --> 00:16:19.854
Hey.

275
00:16:19.985 --> 00:16:23.031
Honey. she's not here.
She's not gonna hurt you.

276
00:16:23.162 --> 00:16:24.641
Promise?

277
00:16:24.772 --> 00:16:26.252
Yeah. I promise.

278
00:16:30.560 --> 00:16:32.388
Come on.

279
00:16:37.567 --> 00:16:38.568
Where should I...?

280
00:16:38.699 --> 00:16:40.309
[Door opening]

281
00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:43.051
Wow.
Look at all this stuff.

282
00:16:50.667 --> 00:16:52.104
Hey.

283
00:16:52.234 --> 00:16:53.540
Don't touch anything.

284
00:16:53.670 --> 00:16:55.629
Why?

285
00:16:55.759 --> 00:16:58.458
Because this-- this used to
belong to other people.

286
00:16:58.588 --> 00:17:00.025
The people
who lived here?

287
00:17:00.155 --> 00:17:01.069
Mm-hmm.

288
00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:02.418
Oh.

289
00:17:04.290 --> 00:17:07.380
It's like the cavern
of the lonely dragon.

290
00:17:07.510 --> 00:17:09.208
Yeah?

291
00:17:09.338 --> 00:17:12.254
When the Cromenockle was
lost in the rainbow sky.

292
00:17:12.385 --> 00:17:15.518
she found a cavern where
the lonely dragon lived.

293
00:17:15.649 --> 00:17:19.174
and it was full of stuff
that nobody wanted.

294
00:17:19.305 --> 00:17:23.352
But for the lonely dragon.

295
00:17:23.483 --> 00:17:25.398
all the stuff was treasure.
And guess what.

296
00:17:25.528 --> 00:17:26.834
What?

297
00:17:26.965 --> 00:17:29.532
In one of the
big piles of stuff.

298
00:17:29.663 --> 00:17:32.927
there was the map
of the rainbow sky.

299
00:17:33.058 --> 00:17:36.757
So. the lonely dragon
gave it to the Cromenockle

300
00:17:36.887 --> 00:17:38.585
and then she
wasn't lost anymore.

301
00:17:38.715 --> 00:17:41.283
So maybe we'll
find a map in here.

302
00:17:41.414 --> 00:17:44.243
Yeah. maybe we will.

303
00:17:53.165 --> 00:17:54.688
Mom?

304
00:17:54.818 --> 00:17:56.472
Yeah.

305
00:17:56.603 --> 00:17:58.387
What's wrong?

306
00:18:00.868 --> 00:18:03.131
Nothing.

307
00:18:07.135 --> 00:18:10.660
[Jade] Yeah. this is it.
this one. right here.

308
00:18:14.969 --> 00:18:16.406
Oh. this'll
never work.

309
00:18:16.536 --> 00:18:17.929
Of course.
it's going to work.

310
00:18:18.059 --> 00:18:21.324
No. it's not
nearly tall enough.

311
00:18:21.454 --> 00:18:22.847
It won't have
the signal strength.

312
00:18:22.977 --> 00:18:24.675
Yeah. listen. we can
deal with that. okay?

313
00:18:24.805 --> 00:18:27.330
This is just a test run.
Look. you're an engineer. right?

314
00:18:27.460 --> 00:18:28.766
Amusement parks?

315
00:18:28.896 --> 00:18:30.550
Yeah.

316
00:18:30.681 --> 00:18:32.596
Okay. So. I guess that
means one of us built

317
00:18:32.726 --> 00:18:34.554
a multi-million-dollar
software company

318
00:18:34.685 --> 00:18:37.557
and the other does. what.
safety tests on the teacup ride?

319
00:18:40.517 --> 00:18:43.737
You know what?
Do it yourself.

320
00:18:43.868 --> 00:18:46.392
Huh? Wait. no. no! Hey. look.
I'm sorry. okay? I'm sorry.

321
00:18:46.523 --> 00:18:48.351
People tell me I'm not great
when it comes to

322
00:18:48.481 --> 00:18:49.526
talking to people.

323
00:18:49.656 --> 00:18:50.788
You have no idea
what it's like

324
00:18:50.918 --> 00:18:52.442
being smarter
than everyone you know.

325
00:18:52.572 --> 00:18:54.922
Listen. okay. look.
the truth is...

326
00:18:55.053 --> 00:18:56.837
I could really
use your help.

327
00:18:56.968 --> 00:18:59.971
Yeah. you could.

328
00:18:59.772 --> 00:19:03.298
This antenna.
it has to go up high.

329
00:19:03.428 --> 00:19:06.083
That is the highest tree that I
could find. but I-- I can't.

330
00:19:06.214 --> 00:19:08.607
[Stammers] I get vertigo.

331
00:19:09.782 --> 00:19:11.523
So. you brought me
out here to climb a tree?

332
00:19:14.657 --> 00:19:15.614
Yeah.

333
00:19:15.745 --> 00:19:17.138
[Scoffs]

334
00:19:17.268 --> 00:19:18.574
Listen.
you don't like me.

335
00:19:18.704 --> 00:19:19.880
All right? That's fine.

336
00:19:22.578 --> 00:19:24.623
But if there's even
the slightest chance

337
00:19:24.754 --> 00:19:28.627
this could work.
don't you want to know for sure?

338
00:19:31.543 --> 00:19:34.895
Yeah. Yeah. I do.

339
00:19:37.462 --> 00:19:39.987
Okay.

340
00:19:40.117 --> 00:19:41.379
All right.

341
00:19:47.951 --> 00:19:50.388
All right.
Pass me up the cable?

342
00:19:51.650 --> 00:19:56.394
[Birds chirping]

343
00:20:10.278 --> 00:20:12.584
Kristi. you here?

344
00:20:24.205 --> 00:20:34.084
♪

345
00:20:55.279 --> 00:20:57.368
[Kristi] Sheriff Boyd?

346
00:20:57.499 --> 00:21:00.632
Kristi. hey.

347
00:21:00.763 --> 00:21:02.417
I-I was just. uh...

348
00:21:02.547 --> 00:21:03.548
I didn't see
you upstairs. so...

349
00:21:03.679 --> 00:21:06.290
Everything okay?

350
00:21:06.421 --> 00:21:09.293
I know you and Kenny are close.
and I was just. uh...

351
00:21:09.424 --> 00:21:11.643
How's he doing?

352
00:21:11.774 --> 00:21:14.603
Well. I mean...

353
00:21:14.733 --> 00:21:18.346
I think he's...
been having a hard time since...

354
00:21:18.476 --> 00:21:20.391
Right. right.

355
00:21:20.522 --> 00:21:22.437
And I-I think he's
trying really hard

356
00:21:22.567 --> 00:21:24.352
to be this person that he
thinks people need him to be.

357
00:21:24.482 --> 00:21:26.267
if that makes sense?

358
00:21:26.397 --> 00:21:27.833
Yeah.

359
00:21:27.964 --> 00:21:30.575
Being your deputy and...

360
00:21:30.706 --> 00:21:33.274
and I know
a big thing for him

361
00:21:33.404 --> 00:21:35.319
is he doesn't want
to let you down.

362
00:21:35.450 --> 00:21:38.844
I know. And I'm really trying
not to push him too hard.

363
00:21:38.975 --> 00:21:40.716
The truth is. he needs
to be ready to lead.

364
00:21:40.846 --> 00:21:42.239
Can I be honest
with you?

365
00:21:42.370 --> 00:21:44.502
Please.

366
00:21:44.633 --> 00:21:46.722
I get that you want to
prepare him for the worst.

367
00:21:46.852 --> 00:21:49.725
get him ready to take your
place in case something ever...

368
00:21:51.857 --> 00:21:54.295
But right now.
he's really hurting.

369
00:21:54.425 --> 00:21:56.340
and I don't think
he needs a sheriff.

370
00:21:56.471 --> 00:21:59.039
I think he needs a dad.

371
00:22:00.779 --> 00:22:03.217
Goddamn it.

372
00:22:03.347 --> 00:22:04.653
I'm sorry. I...

373
00:22:04.783 --> 00:22:05.958
No. no. no.

374
00:22:06.089 --> 00:22:08.352
It's...
It's not you. It's me.

375
00:22:08.483 --> 00:22:10.659
It's...
[Sighs]

376
00:22:10.789 --> 00:22:12.487
If you don't learn
from your mistakes.

377
00:22:12.617 --> 00:22:13.966
you're doomed to
repeat them. right?

378
00:22:14.097 --> 00:22:17.535
[Kristi]
I really didn't mean to...

379
00:22:17.666 --> 00:22:19.276
[Boyd] You didn't.
[Stammers] No apology.

380
00:22:22.714 --> 00:22:24.412
Thank you. Kristi.

381
00:22:34.465 --> 00:22:44.388
♪

382
00:22:46.956 --> 00:22:50.916
People think the
Bible's a fixed object -

383
00:22:51.047 --> 00:22:53.397
something written.
completed.

384
00:22:55.138 --> 00:22:56.705
But how can
the story be finished

385
00:22:56.835 --> 00:23:00.622
if all the players
remain on stage?

386
00:23:00.752 --> 00:23:02.493
We call it
"the Good Book". but...

387
00:23:05.235 --> 00:23:09.283
Did you know it's actually
comprised of 73 books?

388
00:23:09.413 --> 00:23:10.240
Did you know that?

389
00:23:13.069 --> 00:23:16.464
Matthew. Mark.

390
00:23:16.594 --> 00:23:18.640
Romans. Corinthians.

391
00:23:18.770 --> 00:23:20.511
Seventy-three books.

392
00:23:21.860 --> 00:23:25.603
All filled with tales
of miracle and wonder.

393
00:23:30.869 --> 00:23:34.351
But there's also
darkness in the Bible.

394
00:23:34.482 --> 00:23:37.354
Gruesome. horrible things.

395
00:23:37.485 --> 00:23:39.269
You know. since--

396
00:23:39.400 --> 00:23:43.447
since the night I arrived.

397
00:23:43.578 --> 00:23:46.711
there seems to be a question
I keep coming back to.

398
00:23:52.587 --> 00:23:55.285
Seventy-three books.

399
00:23:56.547 --> 00:23:59.333
What if we.

400
00:23:59.463 --> 00:24:03.163
the people of this town.

401
00:24:03.293 --> 00:24:06.253
are living the book
that has yet to be written?

402
00:24:07.515 --> 00:24:10.387
What if this is Book 74?

403
00:24:13.695 --> 00:24:18.265
And. Sara.
what if we were chosen?

404
00:24:19.657 --> 00:24:21.311
For what?

405
00:24:24.662 --> 00:24:26.795
I don't know.

406
00:24:30.668 --> 00:24:33.541
Which is why I need you to
tell me about these voices.

407
00:24:38.937 --> 00:24:40.330
Please.

408
00:24:47.598 --> 00:24:50.210
[Ethan]
When's Dad coming home?

409
00:24:51.689 --> 00:24:53.169
[Exhales]
Soon. honey.

410
00:24:53.300 --> 00:24:55.563
I don't think
he will be much longer.

411
00:24:59.123 --> 00:25:00.429
What's wrong?

412
00:25:02.779 --> 00:25:05.695
Nothing. I'm just--

413
00:25:05.825 --> 00:25:08.480
just admiring this piece
of lonely dragon's treasure.

414
00:25:08.611 --> 00:25:10.482
It's pretty.

415
00:25:11.875 --> 00:25:13.442
Yeah.

416
00:25:16.096 --> 00:25:19.012
Why does that light
keep turning off?

417
00:25:22.799 --> 00:25:24.496
I don't know.

418
00:25:25.628 --> 00:25:28.587
How about you
and I have an adventure?

419
00:25:28.718 --> 00:25:30.546
What kind of adventure?

420
00:25:30.676 --> 00:25:33.810
Mm. some sort of.
um. treasure hunt.

421
00:25:33.940 --> 00:25:35.507
Really?

422
00:25:35.638 --> 00:25:36.813
Mm-hmm.

423
00:25:36.943 --> 00:25:38.728
Yeah. the game's
gonna be called.

424
00:25:38.858 --> 00:25:41.513
"Where does
the light come from?"

425
00:25:41.644 --> 00:25:43.254
Sounds good?

426
00:25:43.385 --> 00:25:45.691
-Yeah.
-Let's do it.

427
00:25:45.822 --> 00:25:49.521
Let's go. Okay.
we will need some tools. right?

428
00:25:49.652 --> 00:25:50.522
Mm-hmm.

429
00:25:50.653 --> 00:25:53.438
Ooh. I found your tool!

430
00:25:54.657 --> 00:25:57.747
Let's see if I've...

431
00:25:57.877 --> 00:25:59.183
found my tool.

432
00:26:00.663 --> 00:26:02.882
Okay.

433
00:26:05.711 --> 00:26:07.060
Let's move this.

434
00:26:07.191 --> 00:26:10.455
Come on. honey.
I need you to push. Help me.

435
00:26:15.678 --> 00:26:17.723
Okeydokey.

436
00:26:17.854 --> 00:26:19.595
Now. this is your tool.

437
00:26:19.725 --> 00:26:22.119
This is my tool. Ready?

438
00:26:23.816 --> 00:26:24.513
[Ethan] Mom!

439
00:26:27.037 --> 00:26:29.431
You're doin' great!

440
00:26:36.002 --> 00:26:37.787
Here we go.

441
00:26:44.968 --> 00:26:46.796
Hey. I'm snagged somewhere.
Can you see where it's caught?

442
00:26:46.926 --> 00:26:49.494
Uh. no. not really.

443
00:26:49.625 --> 00:26:51.453
Just. uh. give it a shake.
see if you can wiggle it free.

444
00:26:55.065 --> 00:26:56.675
Yeah. that's it.

445
00:26:56.806 --> 00:26:58.938
-[Jade] You got it?
-Yup.

446
00:27:05.031 --> 00:27:06.903
All right.

447
00:27:07.033 --> 00:27:09.558
Okay.
How you doing up there?

448
00:27:09.688 --> 00:27:11.603
[Jim] Doing good.

449
00:27:12.648 --> 00:27:14.476
Fuck!

450
00:27:15.868 --> 00:27:17.653
Oh. Jesus.

451
00:27:17.783 --> 00:27:18.610
[Breathing heavily]

452
00:27:22.092 --> 00:27:25.051
[Gasps in horror]

453
00:27:25.182 --> 00:27:29.534
[Breathing heavily]

454
00:27:44.114 --> 00:27:45.768
No. no. no! No!

455
00:27:45.898 --> 00:27:46.856
-[Gunshot]
-[Screaming]

456
00:27:50.207 --> 00:27:52.644
[Screaming indistinctly]

457
00:27:52.775 --> 00:27:56.518
[Screaming]

458
00:28:00.783 --> 00:28:01.610
[Screams]

459
00:28:06.136 --> 00:28:07.659
No. no. no! No. no!

460
00:28:07.790 --> 00:28:09.835
[Groans]

461
00:28:09.966 --> 00:28:12.055
[Gasping for breath]

462
00:28:12.185 --> 00:28:13.883
No. no!

463
00:28:14.013 --> 00:28:15.624
[Gasping for breath]

464
00:28:15.754 --> 00:28:19.802
[Jim] Hey. Hey.

465
00:28:19.932 --> 00:28:21.804
Jade. wh--

466
00:28:21.934 --> 00:28:24.807
Jade. Jade. right here.
Right here.

467
00:28:24.937 --> 00:28:27.200
Listen. whatever it is.
it's not real. Okay?

468
00:28:27.331 --> 00:28:29.986
There's nothing there.

469
00:28:30.116 --> 00:28:31.857
Jade. I'm going
to help you up.

470
00:28:31.988 --> 00:28:33.642
Come here.
Come here.

471
00:28:33.772 --> 00:28:35.818
You okay? Huh?

472
00:28:35.948 --> 00:28:37.167
Just get your
fucking hands off me!

473
00:28:37.297 --> 00:28:38.777
What did you see?

474
00:28:38.908 --> 00:28:40.736
Just fuck off. all right?

475
00:28:46.089 --> 00:28:48.918
They said they wanted to help.

476
00:28:49.048 --> 00:28:51.224
That they'd been here
a long time

477
00:28:51.355 --> 00:28:52.878
and they'd been waiting

478
00:28:53.009 --> 00:28:55.794
for someone to come
who would hear them.

479
00:28:55.925 --> 00:28:57.753
someone who could help them.

480
00:28:57.883 --> 00:28:59.058
Help them do what?

481
00:28:59.189 --> 00:29:01.191
Help them escape.

482
00:29:01.321 --> 00:29:03.367
Help them go home.

483
00:29:03.497 --> 00:29:06.196
They said they were
just like us.

484
00:29:06.326 --> 00:29:10.853
But why?
Why did you believe them?

485
00:29:10.983 --> 00:29:14.900
Because...
they told me things.

486
00:29:15.031 --> 00:29:18.338
things they couldn't know.

487
00:29:18.469 --> 00:29:21.951
They told me those
two cars were coming

488
00:29:22.081 --> 00:29:25.737
and to stand out near the edge
of town and I would see.

489
00:29:26.433 --> 00:29:28.784
They said it happened before.

490
00:29:28.914 --> 00:29:33.005
that two cars came
on the same day

491
00:29:33.136 --> 00:29:36.182
and everyone died.

492
00:29:36.313 --> 00:29:38.837
They said it was because of the
people in the cars. but if...

493
00:29:41.971 --> 00:29:45.235
...if I did what they said.

494
00:29:45.365 --> 00:29:49.065
that we'd be safe.
we'd get to go home.

495
00:29:50.936 --> 00:29:53.199
Okay. How?

496
00:29:53.330 --> 00:29:57.943
How would we get to go home?

497
00:30:02.339 --> 00:30:04.558
-I don't know.
-Okay.

498
00:30:04.689 --> 00:30:08.475
Do you still believe that
they were telling the truth?

499
00:30:08.606 --> 00:30:12.828
They promised...
that Nathan would be okay.

500
00:30:15.047 --> 00:30:18.050
They-they promised.
and now. now he's...

501
00:30:18.181 --> 00:30:21.010
[Screaming]

502
00:30:21.140 --> 00:30:22.402
-Sara.
-[Screaming]

503
00:30:22.533 --> 00:30:23.882
Sara. listen to me.
Come here.

504
00:30:24.013 --> 00:30:26.058
Listen to me.
Listen to me. Sara.

505
00:30:26.189 --> 00:30:28.278
If these voices are real.

506
00:30:28.408 --> 00:30:30.367
if something here is
communicating with you.

507
00:30:30.497 --> 00:30:32.282
then that means you're
connected to this place

508
00:30:32.412 --> 00:30:33.936
in a way that
no one else here is.

509
00:30:34.066 --> 00:30:36.199
and that makes you
incredibly valuable.

510
00:30:36.329 --> 00:30:37.374
Do you understand?

511
00:30:37.504 --> 00:30:39.463
But we need proof.

512
00:30:39.593 --> 00:30:43.119
We need to be able
to go to Sheriff Boyd

513
00:30:43.249 --> 00:30:45.991
and tell him with absolute
certainty that you--

514
00:30:46.122 --> 00:30:47.340
That I'm not crazy.

515
00:30:47.471 --> 00:30:50.039
No. the voices.
that these voices are not simply

516
00:30:50.169 --> 00:30:51.954
the product of a troubled mind.

517
00:30:52.084 --> 00:30:54.086
So. Sara. I need--

518
00:30:54.217 --> 00:30:55.174
Ow!

519
00:30:55.305 --> 00:30:56.349
-Sara?
-Ow.

520
00:30:56.480 --> 00:30:58.308
-What?
-Ow. No!

521
00:30:58.438 --> 00:31:00.527
-What?
-[Screams]

522
00:31:00.658 --> 00:31:02.529
-Sara.
-No! No!

523
00:31:02.660 --> 00:31:04.531
-What?
-No. no. no!

524
00:31:04.662 --> 00:31:07.230
-What?
-Please! Ah. no. no!

525
00:31:07.360 --> 00:31:09.319
-What?
-[Screams]

526
00:31:09.449 --> 00:31:10.886
-Sara. what is it?
-Ah. no!

527
00:31:11.016 --> 00:31:11.974
What?

528
00:31:12.104 --> 00:31:14.150
I need-- I need...

529
00:31:14.280 --> 00:31:15.151
Need what?

530
00:31:15.281 --> 00:31:16.413
Paper.

531
00:31:16.543 --> 00:31:18.154
Paper.

532
00:31:18.284 --> 00:31:20.025
[Gasping]

533
00:31:22.680 --> 00:31:25.204
They want me to
show you something.

534
00:31:25.335 --> 00:31:30.122
[Birds chirping]

535
00:31:48.097 --> 00:31:50.099
[Static buzzing lightly]

536
00:31:50.229 --> 00:31:51.491
[Static buzzing]

537
00:31:53.189 --> 00:31:54.103
[Static buzzing loudly]

538
00:31:54.233 --> 00:31:59.064
[Static buzzing]

539
00:32:03.112 --> 00:32:06.071
Hello?
Is anybody out there?

540
00:32:06.202 --> 00:32:08.247
[Static buzzing lightly]

541
00:32:10.206 --> 00:32:12.425
-Hello?
-[Static buzzing lightly]

542
00:32:14.688 --> 00:32:15.907
Is anybody there?

543
00:32:29.094 --> 00:32:30.182
[Grunts]

544
00:32:33.620 --> 00:32:35.274
[Speaks Cantonese]

545
00:32:35.405 --> 00:32:37.929
I don't want any tea!

546
00:32:39.365 --> 00:32:42.281
[Speaks Cantonese]

547
00:32:44.240 --> 00:32:46.372
You realize I have no
idea what you're saying.

548
00:32:49.114 --> 00:32:50.463
Fine.

549
00:32:58.689 --> 00:33:00.169
It's good.

550
00:33:00.299 --> 00:33:01.823
Thanks.

551
00:33:08.699 --> 00:33:11.223
I keep seeing it.
I-I keep--

552
00:33:11.354 --> 00:33:12.964
[Stammers. sighing]

553
00:33:13.095 --> 00:33:15.445
I keep having these. uh...

554
00:33:15.575 --> 00:33:16.925
[Exhales]

555
00:33:19.797 --> 00:33:22.147
Hey. where are you going?

556
00:33:25.759 --> 00:33:27.239
Hello?

557
00:33:28.458 --> 00:33:29.589
Where'd you go?

558
00:33:39.730 --> 00:33:42.515
Holy shit.

559
00:33:42.646 --> 00:33:45.083
This is all the. uh...

560
00:33:45.214 --> 00:33:47.477
Wow. Oh. wait. wait!
Hold on.

561
00:33:47.607 --> 00:33:49.218
Slow down. Tian.
I got this.

562
00:33:52.177 --> 00:33:55.180
[Exhales]

563
00:33:55.311 --> 00:33:57.095
What--

564
00:33:57.226 --> 00:33:59.010
what are you looking for?

565
00:34:01.491 --> 00:34:03.101
[Clattering]

566
00:34:03.232 --> 00:34:05.277
What is that?
It's a yearbook.

567
00:34:05.408 --> 00:34:07.540
1972?
How many people...?

568
00:34:09.368 --> 00:34:11.457
[Speaks Cantonese]

569
00:34:11.588 --> 00:34:13.720
Okay.

570
00:34:13.851 --> 00:34:16.506
Well. I mean. could you tell me
what you're looking for?

571
00:34:16.636 --> 00:34:18.508
Shh.

572
00:34:21.641 --> 00:34:22.991
What's that?

573
00:34:27.473 --> 00:34:28.605
Hmm?

574
00:34:40.051 --> 00:34:45.883
♪

575
00:34:46.014 --> 00:34:50.148
[Breathing rapidly]
Oh. what the fuck?

576
00:34:50.279 --> 00:34:54.718
[Sara gasping. whimpering]

577
00:34:59.201 --> 00:35:03.509
[Whimpering]

578
00:35:03.640 --> 00:35:04.597
Please...

579
00:35:04.728 --> 00:35:06.730
I can't...

580
00:35:06.860 --> 00:35:11.082
[Breathing heavily]

581
00:35:11.213 --> 00:35:13.650
[Gasps]

582
00:35:13.780 --> 00:35:17.306
[Breathing heavily]

583
00:35:19.873 --> 00:35:23.225
[Breathing heavily]

584
00:35:26.706 --> 00:35:30.058
I don't...

585
00:35:30.188 --> 00:35:32.408
What is this?

586
00:35:32.538 --> 00:35:34.932
They said...

587
00:35:35.063 --> 00:35:39.589
They said they watched you
on the day you got here.

588
00:35:39.719 --> 00:35:43.288
They said they
watched you bury the bag

589
00:35:43.419 --> 00:35:45.638
and that this is proof
that they're real.

590
00:35:50.861 --> 00:35:52.558
Do you know what that means?

591
00:35:52.689 --> 00:35:54.778
[inhales deeply]

592
00:36:10.707 --> 00:36:11.664
Oh!

593
00:36:16.887 --> 00:36:18.323
Ah! Here we go.

594
00:36:19.585 --> 00:36:20.412
Okay.

595
00:36:22.458 --> 00:36:23.850
Yeah.

596
00:36:23.981 --> 00:36:27.680
That's it.
There we go.

597
00:36:30.205 --> 00:36:31.162
Hey.

598
00:36:31.293 --> 00:36:32.511
Sheriff Boyd.

599
00:36:35.775 --> 00:36:36.776
Ladies.

600
00:36:36.907 --> 00:36:38.430
Hi!

601
00:36:38.561 --> 00:36:41.042
[Chattering]

602
00:36:43.305 --> 00:36:44.480
Fuck!

603
00:36:46.308 --> 00:36:47.657
[Knocking]

604
00:36:47.787 --> 00:36:48.832
Come in.

605
00:36:48.962 --> 00:36:50.312
[Door opening]

606
00:36:50.442 --> 00:36:51.487
[Boyd] Hey.

607
00:36:51.617 --> 00:36:53.054
[Door closing]

608
00:36:58.059 --> 00:37:02.063
I was. uh. going through my
things back at the station.

609
00:37:02.193 --> 00:37:05.501
and I realized I haven't thrown
a ball around in a while.

610
00:37:05.631 --> 00:37:07.329
Come on outside.

611
00:37:07.459 --> 00:37:09.244
You can help an old man
knock the rust off.

612
00:37:09.374 --> 00:37:11.202
I'm good.

613
00:37:14.771 --> 00:37:17.252
Hey. I ever tell
you. uh.

614
00:37:17.382 --> 00:37:19.515
I played first base
back in college.

615
00:37:19.645 --> 00:37:21.343
No.

616
00:37:21.473 --> 00:37:22.996
Yeah. I was
pretty good too.

617
00:37:23.127 --> 00:37:25.825
Had a couple scouts
kicking around.

618
00:37:25.956 --> 00:37:28.654
Here I am.
18 years old. thinkin'.

619
00:37:28.785 --> 00:37:31.657
"Man. I might
be going to the show.

620
00:37:31.788 --> 00:37:34.878
"be the next Willie McCovey."

621
00:37:35.008 --> 00:37:36.793
What happened?

622
00:37:39.404 --> 00:37:43.278
Oh. you know...

623
00:37:43.408 --> 00:37:45.193
life had other plans.

624
00:37:48.848 --> 00:37:51.503
Life always seems
to have other plans.

625
00:37:59.816 --> 00:38:01.122
I'm sick. Kenny.

626
00:38:05.517 --> 00:38:06.953
What do you...?

627
00:38:07.084 --> 00:38:09.304
Have you talked
to Kristi about it?

628
00:38:09.434 --> 00:38:12.437
Not that kind of sick.

629
00:38:12.568 --> 00:38:14.744
My father was diagnosed
with Parkinson's

630
00:38:14.874 --> 00:38:16.485
when he was around my age.

631
00:38:16.615 --> 00:38:18.965
It's not supposed
to be hereditary.

632
00:38:19.096 --> 00:38:20.358
The doctors all
swore up and down

633
00:38:20.489 --> 00:38:23.405
how extremely rare
that would be.

634
00:38:23.535 --> 00:38:26.451
Wrong time to win
the lottery. I guess.

635
00:38:26.582 --> 00:38:30.890
But how do you know that...?
How do you know?

636
00:38:31.021 --> 00:38:32.327
I mean.
it could be anything. right?

637
00:38:32.457 --> 00:38:33.719
It is what it is.

638
00:38:35.982 --> 00:38:39.072
Look...

639
00:38:39.203 --> 00:38:41.945
this thing is already
chipping away at me.

640
00:38:43.381 --> 00:38:46.515
And eventually. I'm gonna get
to the point where I can't--

641
00:38:46.645 --> 00:38:51.607
I'm not gonna be able to protect
these people anymore.

642
00:38:51.737 --> 00:38:55.828
So I gotta find us a way out
while I still can.

643
00:38:55.959 --> 00:38:58.396
You understand?

644
00:38:58.527 --> 00:39:01.182
The only way
I can do this

645
00:39:01.312 --> 00:39:03.271
is because I know these people
are gonna be in good hands

646
00:39:03.401 --> 00:39:04.924
when I'm gone.

647
00:39:07.536 --> 00:39:09.407
There's a lot of folks
in this town

648
00:39:09.538 --> 00:39:13.629
who are alive today
because of you.

649
00:39:13.759 --> 00:39:16.719
And I know your dad
isn't around to say it.

650
00:39:16.849 --> 00:39:19.461
but I promise you...

651
00:39:19.591 --> 00:39:21.724
he's so goddamn proud of you.

652
00:39:23.073 --> 00:39:24.901
I'm proud of you.

653
00:39:25.031 --> 00:39:28.426
But if you tell me
right now

654
00:39:28.557 --> 00:39:30.863
that you are not ready
for me to go.

655
00:39:30.994 --> 00:39:35.041
that you need more time.

656
00:39:35.172 --> 00:39:37.348
then I ain't
going nowhere.

657
00:39:37.479 --> 00:39:39.872
Okay?

658
00:39:40.003 --> 00:39:41.874
[Exhales]

659
00:39:53.103 --> 00:39:55.584

660
00:39:55.310 --> 00:39:57.486
Well. we doing
this or what?

661
00:39:59.140 --> 00:40:00.968
Doing it.

662
00:40:04.624 --> 00:40:08.846
Hey? Anybody here?

663
00:40:08.976 --> 00:40:12.327
We might be onto something
with this radio.

664
00:40:12.458 --> 00:40:14.112
We're gonna have to get it
higher up. but it could...

665
00:40:18.159 --> 00:40:19.247
What the fuck?

666
00:40:19.378 --> 00:40:22.163
[Footsteps approaching]

667
00:40:22.294 --> 00:40:24.122
[Grunting]
Hi. Dad.

668
00:40:24.252 --> 00:40:25.427
Hey. kiddo.

669
00:40:25.558 --> 00:40:26.689
What you up to?

670
00:40:26.820 --> 00:40:28.039
We're on an adventure.

671
00:40:28.169 --> 00:40:29.692
There's a lot of dirt.

672
00:40:29.823 --> 00:40:32.086
so mom said I should
bring some outside.

673
00:40:32.217 --> 00:40:33.566
Uh-huh.
And where is your mother?

674
00:40:33.696 --> 00:40:34.915
[Ethan]
In the basement.

675
00:40:36.177 --> 00:40:40.616
[Clattering]

676
00:40:42.357 --> 00:40:46.666
[Clattering]

677
00:40:46.796 --> 00:40:51.540
[Shovel clattering]

678
00:40:51.671 --> 00:40:55.893
[Clattering]

679
00:40:58.199 --> 00:40:59.592
Tabitha?

680
00:40:59.722 --> 00:41:03.030
Hey. Hey.
How'd things go?

681
00:41:03.161 --> 00:41:04.292
Good.

682
00:41:04.423 --> 00:41:05.598
Yeah?

683
00:41:05.728 --> 00:41:07.339
We got some static. so...

684
00:41:07.469 --> 00:41:09.210
Yeah. well.
that's wonderful. right?

685
00:41:09.341 --> 00:41:11.038
Yeah. it's a start.

686
00:41:11.169 --> 00:41:12.822
What you doing?

687
00:41:12.953 --> 00:41:14.737
It's like you
said this morning.

688
00:41:14.868 --> 00:41:18.219
it has to come from somewhere.
right? The electricity.

689
00:41:18.350 --> 00:41:21.657
There's no power lines.
and all the wires.

690
00:41:21.788 --> 00:41:23.398
all the cords. they just...

691
00:41:23.529 --> 00:41:26.358
they just go down.
straight down.

692
00:41:26.488 --> 00:41:30.101
It's so weird.

693
00:41:30.231 --> 00:41:33.104
Okay. Uh. sorry. can you...

694
00:41:33.234 --> 00:41:35.019
not dig for a moment?

695
00:41:35.149 --> 00:41:36.063
Yes.

696
00:41:38.805 --> 00:41:40.198
What's going on?

697
00:41:40.328 --> 00:41:42.983
[Sighing]
Okay.

698
00:41:45.333 --> 00:41:47.553
Do you remember
the bracelet I made you?

699
00:41:49.120 --> 00:41:50.948
The what?

700
00:41:51.078 --> 00:41:53.341
The bracelet I made you
after our first few dates.

701
00:41:53.472 --> 00:41:55.213
from. uh. the laces of
your father's boots.

702
00:41:55.343 --> 00:41:56.779
Yeah. of course. I remember.

703
00:41:56.910 --> 00:41:58.172
Okay. Remember.

704
00:41:58.303 --> 00:42:01.088
you lost it at the hospital
the night Julie was born.

705
00:42:01.219 --> 00:42:03.177
Okay.

706
00:42:03.308 --> 00:42:06.006
Turn around.
Look what's sitting there.

707
00:42:12.143 --> 00:42:13.274
[Scoffs]

708
00:42:19.628 --> 00:42:21.369
Okay. I still don't get it.

709
00:42:21.500 --> 00:42:23.197
You're saying
you found a bracelet

710
00:42:23.328 --> 00:42:24.546
that's similar to
the one you gave--

711
00:42:24.677 --> 00:42:26.374
No. no. no. no.
It's not similar.

712
00:42:26.505 --> 00:42:28.159
That is the bracelet.
Those are the laces

713
00:42:28.289 --> 00:42:29.203
from your father's boots!

714
00:42:29.334 --> 00:42:31.205
No. those were generic
rawhide laces.

715
00:42:31.336 --> 00:42:33.381
the same you'd find on any boot.

716
00:42:33.512 --> 00:42:36.341
No. no. no. no. no. no.
Look. Look at this.

717
00:42:36.471 --> 00:42:37.342
Look at this.

718
00:42:37.472 --> 00:42:38.952
What?

719
00:42:39.083 --> 00:42:41.694
This was an accident.
I made this.

720
00:42:41.824 --> 00:42:44.392
I was so afraid I ruined it.
but then. when I gave it to you.

721
00:42:44.523 --> 00:42:45.524
you said. "Accidents--"

722
00:42:45.654 --> 00:42:47.091
"Accidents are the best part."

723
00:42:47.221 --> 00:42:48.962
Yes. Why?

724
00:42:49.093 --> 00:42:50.442
Ah. because it makes
it one of a kind.

725
00:42:50.572 --> 00:42:52.052
Exactly.

726
00:42:57.318 --> 00:42:59.451
It's impossible.

727
00:42:59.581 --> 00:43:01.714
Jim. everything
about this is impossible.

728
00:43:01.844 --> 00:43:03.237
That doesn't
make any sense.

729
00:43:03.368 --> 00:43:06.023
Those wires
don't make sense.

730
00:43:06.153 --> 00:43:08.503
We may not be able to
find out how this got here.

731
00:43:08.634 --> 00:43:11.332
but we can find out
where those wires go.

732
00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:16.163
Give me the shovel.

733
00:43:21.647 --> 00:43:25.303
[Breathing heavily]

734
00:43:25.433 --> 00:43:28.306
[Grunting]

735
00:43:32.571 --> 00:43:37.184
[Breathing heavily]

736
00:43:41.536 --> 00:43:51.459
♪

737
00:44:27.713 --> 00:44:32.413
[indistinct chatter]

738
00:44:35.068 --> 00:44:36.591
Where's yours?

739
00:44:36.722 --> 00:44:37.897
First base.
I don't need no glove.

740
00:44:38.027 --> 00:44:39.855
[Laughs]

741
00:44:39.986 --> 00:44:41.683
Are you sure?
Because I got some heat.

742
00:44:41.814 --> 00:44:43.642
Just throw the damn ball.

743
00:44:43.772 --> 00:44:45.731
You're gonna regret this.

744
00:44:45.861 --> 00:44:48.255
I hear a lot of talking.
but I'm not--

745
00:44:48.386 --> 00:44:48.777
Here comes the heat.

746
00:44:53.652 --> 00:44:58.483
I think. uh--
think maybe I'll carve us a bat.

747
00:44:58.613 --> 00:45:02.530
That way. when you get back.
we can do this right.

748
00:45:02.661 --> 00:45:04.793
When I get back. huh?

749
00:45:06.099 --> 00:45:08.275
Yeah. when you get back.

750
00:45:08.406 --> 00:45:18.285
♪

751
00:45:19.721 --> 00:45:21.288
Yeah.

752
00:45:27.773 --> 00:45:32.517
[Quiet snoring]

753
00:45:39.437 --> 00:45:42.657
[Snoring]

754
00:45:42.788 --> 00:45:46.400
[Passionate moaning]

755
00:45:46.531 --> 00:45:48.359
[Snoring]

756
00:45:48.489 --> 00:45:50.361
[Passionate moaning]

757
00:45:50.491 --> 00:45:53.755
[Snoring]

758
00:46:01.894 --> 00:46:11.773
♪

759
00:46:42.543 --> 00:46:44.719
They're so beautiful.

760
00:46:46.634 --> 00:46:49.115
I'm so glad you like them.

761
00:46:49.246 --> 00:46:51.900
When can I come inside?

762
00:46:54.468 --> 00:46:56.383
♪

